I was able to do that and get some essential features added to the buttons and sliders.
I also made a pre client meeting diagramsThe workflow has been good, we have been doing a lot of meetings in person which helps get everyone on the same page quicker.

We are a bit scattered with communication platforms but its ok.
I think everything is going pretty good but for me the research on how to work with python/matplotlib/skimage for images in a GUI is a bit hard to pin down but i'm learning a lot.
At the moment im trying to figure out how to access the segment boundary mask and use the values to select individual super pixels and turn them into buttons for opening a split function.
Seems like it should be able to work but i am going to research if there is something better tomorrow.
Any thoughts on that would be great.

I think i probably should have spent more time this week looking at related works but i am happy to get the sliders working because i learned alot about how the gui and python functions work so happy with that.
